{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change procedure to require MPs to formally record reasons for abstention",
        "additional_details": "Currently, constituents face a disadvantage when evaluating their representatives if they abstain from voting, as there is limited information available. Reasons for an abstention could include; the impartiality of the chair, party abstentionist policy, personal choice to abstain, procedural reasons, constituency or ministerial duties, or other unforeseen circumstances. \r\n \r\nThis procedural change aims to eliminate this ambiguity by requiring a clear reason for abstention, ensuring transparency for constituents.\r\n",
        "background": "When a division is called, a vote is taken, and participating MPs' positions are recorded. However, when an MP abstains, there is no clear record provided. This procedural change aims to reduce ambiguity and ensure transparency by requiring MPs to formally state their reasons for abstaining.",
